Tips and Tricks:
Windows 11 is only available for rounds 1 and 2, so make sure you learn Windows Server as well, or something else, to be helpful later on in the competition
Here’s a detailed documentation template your students can use. It’s structured for clarity, consistency, and professionalism:
CyberPatriot Best Practices & Scripts Documentation Template
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.. Introduction
Purpose: Explain why this documentation exists (e.g., to share knowledge, improve future performance).
Audience: Who should use this document (future teams, instructors, etc.).
Scope: What systems and tasks are covered (Windows, Linux, Networking, etc.).
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Environment Setup
Tools Required:
[List tools: e.g., PowerShell, Bash, CyberPatriot VM images]
Initial Configuration:
Steps for setting up Windows/Linux VMs.
Network configuration basics.
Security Baseline:
Default hardening steps before competition starts.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Best Practices
Organize by category:
Windows Hardening
Disable unnecessary services.
Apply Group Policy settings.
Enable firewall and configure rules.
Linux Hardening
Update packages.
Configure iptables or ufw.
Remove unused users and groups.
Networking
Secure router settings.
Change default passwords.
Enable WPA2 encryption.
Time Management
Divide tasks by OS.
Prioritize scoring items first.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Scripts & Automation
For each script, include:
Script Name: [e.g., disable_services.ps1]\ Purpose: [Explain what it does]\ Usage:
# Example command to run
powershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File disable_services.ps1
Code Snippet:
# Disable unnecessary Windows services
Set-Service
Notes:
Tested on Windows 10 CyberPatriot image.
Requires admin privileges.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Troubleshooting
Common issues and fixes:
Issue: Firewall blocks scoring server.
Fix: Add exception for scoring IP.
Issue: Script fails due to permissions.
Fix: Run as administrator.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Lessons Learned
What worked well.
What could be improved.
Recommendations for next year.

